> A good gravy has the power to transform a meal. Our festive gravy is just that and can
> be made in advance, simply reheating on the day to save you time. The rich flavours
> of red wine in this one are a classic pairing for your roast beef.

Heat @olive oil{3%tbsp} in a #pot{}. Add @garlic cloves{3} and cook until fragrant.

Add @plain flour{56.25%g} and stir well with a #wooden spoon{} to form a roux.

Pour in @boiling water{1500%ml} gradually, stirring constantly to prevent lumps.

Add @red wine jus paste{66%g} and @beef stock paste{22.5%g}.

Bring to the boil and simmer stirring occasionally for ~{25%minutes} until thickened and
season with @?salt{} and @?ground black pepper{} to taste.

Serve hot as the perfect accompaniment to your roast beef.